<div style="position: relative; height: 15px; width: 100%;"> <a style="float: right;" href="?subtopic=creatures&race=quaraconstrictorscout">next <img src="images/arrow_right.gif" width="15" height="11" border="0"/></a> <a style="position: absolute;" href="?subtopic=creatures&race=priestessofthewildsun"><img src="images/arrow_left.gif" width="15" height="11" border="0"/> previous</a> <div style="position: absolute; width: 80%; margin-left: 10%; margin-right: 10%; text-align: center;"><a href="?subtopic=creatures"><img src="images/arrow_up.gif" width="11" height="15" border="0"/> back</a></div></div><div style="position: relative; top: 25px; clear: both; "><div style="height: 64px; margin-bottom: 5px;"> <h2 style="float: right;">Putrid Mummies</h2> <img src="images/library/putridmummy.gif"/></div><div style="margin-bottom: 35px; clear: both;"> <p>The Putrid Mummy is a stronger and poisonous version of <a href="?subtopic=creatures&race=mummy">Mummies</a>.</p> <p>Putrid Mummies have 1500 hitpoints. They are immune to death and earth damage and cannot be paralysed. Moreover, they are strong against ice damage. On the other hand, they are weak against fire and holy damage. These creatures can neither be summoned nor convinced. In addition, they are able to sense invisible creatures.</p> <p>Putrid Mummies yield 900 experience points. They carry broken flasks, gold coins, green bandages, little bowls of myrrh, single human eyes and sometimes other items with them.</p> </div></div>